Review content: Booked my unwell baby an appointment at 8:30pm at another site which had already closed at 6:30pm - keeping an unwell baby up way past her bed time. Completely unacceptable and a shambles.

This practice‚Äôs negligence put me in hospital for two weeks after I spent ten days being dismissed by doctors who refused to see me in person.I spoke to several doctors over the phone and through their awful eConsult system, but was repeatedly told I wasn‚Äôt an urgent case which made me believe my symptoms were minor. My condition worsened until I had to be admitted to hospital for two weeks.This could easily have been avoided if someone had simply taken the time to see me in person. The complete lack of care, and responsibility was shocking.Avoid at all costs.

Been at this practice for a decade now. I'm really impressed with the new online booking system - hopefully it will free up the phone line for those who really need it. The vast majority of the time the admin team/receptionists have been extremely helpful, going out of their way to support me. GPs have always been friendly, attentive and helpful.

The reception manager Deborah Turner and the rest of the reception staff are incapable of performing receptionist dutiesInstead they masquerade as doctors and attempt to pass medical judgment upon the patients.I wanted to see a GP not speak with a nosey receptionist.

The reception manager Ms Deborah Turner is the resident Karen being arbiter of who is deemed worthy to receive treatment in a timely manner.Please consider replacing the reception staff starting with this individual. The reputation of the practice is already dragged through the mud.

Find it really odd how a non liscend medical practioner, the reception manager Deborah turner is qualified to determine if you are deemed worthy of being seen by a GP.Please consider replacing the reception staff, their job is to book appointments and not diagnose medical conditions.

I have been a patient with this practice since child, my late grand father was with this surgery so my whole family, I hardly visit surgery , recently,  after many years I was given an emmergency appointment to visit the surgery at 12 noon I arrive at 11:30 i made receptionist aware that I had an appointment at 12 noon , I was told to take a seat , a doctor  will call me , 12:30 pm pass no one has called i had to inform the receptionist twis that I have been here awaiting  more than an hour and I am in alot pain I have not been called,  finally at 12:50I was called no apology nothing , my condition was very poorly,  I had very bad chesty flame I wanted to use the bin , however the doctor was racist clearly told me not to make her bin dirty. She asked me to use the tissue instead , the bin is there for a reason , she did not asisst me at all. It was a awful experience. I am considering leaving this surgery,  after many generations.  Services at this surgery is getting poorer.

I have been attending the mission practise for many years and have  always had the best treatment anyone can wish for.. This week I have knee and back pain and was saw Dr Murphy who I understand is fairly new to the practice.. Dr Murphy was attentive  thorough and made me feel comfortable as I was in a lot of pain.. I am very pleased with his diagnosis ..he made me feel more confident about  what has caused my pain and hopefully a cure.   ..
The worst GP ever l seen they book my appointment wrong day and after they did not want to fix even. Rude reception and very bad management

They never pick up the phone or respond worst GP surgery staff .All they do is sit around and chat and leave patients waiting. They give half information told me to bring things like proof of ID when i got to the mission practice . Then said I need to fill up a form . After filling up they said they cant take it in and authorise it because photocopier has not been working for weeks and need to bring a photocopy to what a joke.

If it's not the GPs dismissing brown people for the same issues they've taken white people seriously for it's the receptionist not being able to read. I have booked several appointments requesting a specific GP, waited a month for the appointment each time and getting surprised with the wrong doctor each time. I've written notes, I've called, I've done all that I could to confirm one doctor but the reception team either don't care or need to get themselves checked.

I had a really positive experience at Mission Practice. PA Rahma Mohamed was excellent ‚Äì she listened carefully, explained everything clearly, and carried out all the necessary checks very thoroughly. The tests were done quickly and efficiently, and I felt well looked after throughout the appointment. It‚Äôs reassuring to have such a kind and professional doctor. I would definitely recommend this practice to others.

This has to be some kind of practical joke that they are playing with our tax money. I have been registered to this GP for a couple of years now, and since the day of my registration, I have not been able to see a GP once. I have been ill for the past week and wasn't able to work, I was instructed by a consultant on the phone (111) to pick up a medical certificate which i could later give to my employer. Today I went in to pick up my medical certificate and the receptionist said there is no such document available for me and very rudely told me to call 111 again and "this time listen to what they actually say".I have now changed my GP.

DISGUSTING SERVICE, RUDE AND USELESS RECEPTION STAFF. LINA AND ANISA HAVE ATTITUDE PROBLEMS AND ARE NEVER WILLING TO HELP. THEY GIVE OUT FALSE INFORMATION SO THEY CAN AVOID DOING ANY WORK. HORRIBLE SERVICE FROM THEM BOTH AND AS SOMEONE WHO HAS BEEN WITH A THE MISSION PRACTICE FOR SO MANY YEARS IVE BEVER RECEIVED THE TERRIBLE SERVICE THAT I HAVE BEEN RECEIVING RECENTLY. ALL RECEPTION STAFF ARE INCOMPETENT AND CANNOT ANSWER BASIC QUERIES. THE PHONE RINGS FOR HOURS AND NOT A SINGLE PERSON PICKS UP AND WHEN WE VISIT THE CLINIC THEYRE ALL SITTING HAVE A CHAT. MRS RUTH PLEASE RE TRAIN AND DEVELOP YOUR RECEPTION STAFF. IT WILL BE GOOD FOR THE BUSINESS OVERALL.

I‚Äôve been a patient at this practice since I‚Äôve been a child. I couldn‚Äôt be more grateful for the care and support I‚Äôve received from mission practice. They are always attentive, patient, and thorough, taking the time to listen and explain everything clearly. I never feel rushed during appointments, and I always leave feeling reassured and confident in the treatment plan. Their kindness and professionalism make a huge difference, and it‚Äôs clear they genuinely care about their patients‚Äô wellbeing. I feel very fortunate to have such an excellent GP practice.

I think they should re-name the practice ‚ÄòMission Impossible ‚Äô .I have been receiving Physiotherapy for a Back injury privately & only required a Medical Certificate to ensure I am correctly paid by my Employer. I applied for this under e-consult to limit my use of precious resources & was told this would take 11 days . If I do not supply a valid medical certificate to my employer with 3 days , I will not be paid. This will compound my recovery as I will be stressed about not having money, not being able to pay bills & possibly losing my job. When I explained this to the receptionist ‚ÄòAnn‚Äô , she told me to complain to the Government. Based on my experience this place is awful!I‚Äôm lucky I didn‚Äôt have to wait for a Physiotherapist .

I‚Äôm not sure why this place gets such poor reviews. I submitted a GP request through their website at 9am, received a call back by midday, and had an appointment with a GP at 1pm. By 1:30pm I was finished and on my way. The front-of-house staff were fantastic‚Äîespecially the lovely woman who happened to share the same birthday as me‚Äîand the GP I saw was knowledgeable and thorough. Overall, an excellent experience and great service.
Awful service I really disappointed the receptionist. They are very rude and unprofessional no care for their patients.

You can never get through on the phone, you cannot book an appointment unless you call at 8am and then you get cut off!!! the staff are unhelpful after many attempts I still can't get the authenticator to except im not an imposter! I've got no medication and they couldn't care less
They are never available for appointment requests

The male receptionist i have just spoken to right now at 11:16am on 19.05.2025 was extremely rude im in utter shock with the service this is horrible. I waited on the phone que for so long about my repeated prescription not being notified to my allocated pharmacy just for him to completely dismiss my request and talk over me saying to come in to the clinic without letting me finish my sentence.i responded saying i had an appointment this week but the doctor cancelled so that isnt my fault and i need my prescription urgently. He then proceeded to say i have other people on the line to talk to and ended the call without letting me even speak. The conversation i had with him didnt even last a minute because he wanted to talk over me even though my request was urgent and needed to be dealt with immediately. Im extremely disappointed and can‚Äôt fathom how he can be this disrespectful to a patient with a serious concern.

The doctors at this practice have always been amazing but since Covid the front of house staff are incompetent, unable to deal with simple tasks and if you have an urgent referral for your heart then it‚Äôs not considered urgent by them and they try to fob you off and ask you to fill out an e-consult form that isn‚Äôt working. Or try again tomorrow when we are speaking on the phone now! Totally disgusted by the repeated failings at this surgery, no point in complaining either as they don‚Äôt accept it or have no form of communication path to complain to.

I‚Äôve had a frustrating experience with this practice. I‚Äôve never felt that I could make an appointment unless my situation was extremely severe. Even when I did have appointments, I never felt seen or heard. One appointment went over an hour because the doctor was delayed, but when it was finally my turn, the doctor actually said, ‚Äòwe don‚Äôt have time for all that‚Äô when I tried to voice my concerns. It‚Äôs incredibly frustrating how the e-consult system reaches full capacity, leaving no option for a phone appointment. Another time I called at 12 p.m, they asked to send in photos, and never heard back from them, till after closing hours!!? I get a phone call saying, judging from the photo it‚Äôs severe and that I should‚Äôve come in, when no one contacted me to do so‚Ä¶. I went A&E turns out I had an infection/strep throat. This level of care is unacceptable.

This GP doesn't deserve any stars, absolutely appalled by their service. Remained the first caller for almost an hour and still no response. So glad I moved to another practice, if it wasn't for the location and convenience I'd get my elderly mother and grandmother to move too. Ridiculous.

Have been waiting for an hour and half while being caller No1 on line, just to get Blood Test Results.  Surely, if am caller No1 my call should have been answered by now.  This is atrocious, totally unbelievable and if I was to walk into the surgery, the phones will be not be that busy.  Wish I had a Twitter or social media just to put these receptionist to shame.  Sad times at the NHS.
Some good doctors had been in this place dr webster dr nuns dr Rowell dr wellington now dr gibs the rest give a miss they don‚Äôt listen to you

Thank you so much Dr Adisa for your thoughtful and most importantly thorough Consultation. Thank you for Stressing the importance of taking notes about consultations  and the medications I‚Äôve used , I never realised how much I needed to hear that till you said so . I plan on implementing it from Right Now . Once again Thank you so much , have a great day üòä.

Impossible to get any kind of appointment everything closes not available  Don‚Äôt even bother wast of timeNo help availableEspecially if you work and can‚Äôt be waiting on phone online no help available can‚Äôt book to see anyone ( how can it be this bad )If I could put - stars I would have
Excellent customer service from Mr Tahir (receptionist). Helped me with all my queries. Very polite and great customer support.Thank you so much.

Having now understood how to ask for help online using eConsult at 8am weekdays (my NHS log-in helpful), I cannot rate highly enough the care given to myself and my family, particularly from Dr Hannah, nurse Keisha Walters and healthcare assistant Husna Khatun ‚Äì our various needs always met with kind, helpful, efficient care, thank you.

THIS GP IS THE WORST IN THE WORLDTHE RECEPTION IS BAD & THE DOCTORS ARE NOT EVEN GOODFIND A PROFESSIONAL PLACE THIS ONE IS A JOKE THE DOCTOR WON'T LISTEN TO YOU AND WON'T BE ABLE TO PROPERLY DIAGNOSE YOU.
The service is bad and they don't aswer the call  .kutta  khobis goru i wanna js  . Guyseeeeee dont register this gp  thats tooooooo much baddddddddddd
Cancelled appointment 40 mins to get through. 2 week wait for a telephone call to find out test results. Usless
Something seriously needs to change with the way people book e-consultations and book GP appointments with this clinic. The Phone service is terrible.

I've been coming here since 2017. The service for me has always been very good. My health workers have supported me in my treatments. Without their support I wouldn't be where I am today. My doctors always listen to my concern and always do something about it. Fantastic.

They got very bad reception service. You have to wait four hours to answer the call and they‚Äôre not doing nothing they‚Äôre sitting and eating and joking about. We need to improve our doctor‚Äôs surgery.

Service is extremely poor.We have to wait over an hour to request a prescription. We cannot schedule an appointment when we need one unless we call at 8 a.m. sharp. In most cases, the calls go unanswered and when they are received, the receptionist will advise the caller to call back tomorrow at 8 a.m. Horrible service and very negligent towards their patients.

I have received excellent care at the Mission Practice.Yes, the booking procedure can be difficult if you don‚Äôt have flexibility - but it has also meant I have been able to meet a doctor more quickly than with the old ‚Äòreserve in advance‚Äô system.The receptionists are efficient and helpful in a busy and stressful environment. But most importantly, all the GPs I have dealt with have been very knowledgable and professional. They listen, they explain, and when they say they will call back - they do. In short, they care about their patients.
Worse receptions service, the management needs to improve, look at the reviews and feedback 1.9star
It is sad to be in hold for a few weeks just to get an appointment or for a just a quick call to the customer service. Not recommended.
Very bed service
Honestly this place is better off closing down. I get a quicker response time out of a wall.

Most of the doctors here are fine but it's almost impossible to get an appointment. The phone rings out for an eternity so that in the end you just give up. I have a chronic illness so need to have reasonably easy access to healthcare and the Mission Practice is unable to provide that. Very frustrating.EDIT: They now have system whereby when you call up, if you don't want to wait on hold, you can press '1' and they will  you back when it's your turn.  Sounds like an improvement in theory but, after a couple of hours, I received a text message saying they had tried to contact me and there was no answer. Completely  untrue as my phone was next to me the whole time and I know for a fact it hadn't rung.I then had to ring back and wait on hold, until I eventually got to speak to the reception. I explained that their new call-back system wasn't working properly and the person I spoke to didn't even acknowledge it, so I had to ask if they'd heard me.This practice may not be good at much but they excel in consistently winding their patients up.

The worst gp surgery I have ever come accross !!Been trying to get an appointment for an old grandparent for the past 1 week keep telling me to call 8am and then there‚Äôs nothing available you can never get an appointment at this place they are so unprofessional so rude and don‚Äôt care at all and people at the reception they‚Äôre eating and chatting away phone is ringing they don‚Äôt even care. WORST GP SURGERY EVER !!

I seldom need to visit the GP, but my experiences over the past 15 years have consistently been disappointing. I had composed an extensive message detailing the subpar service provided, but I questioned the purpose of sending it. The last straw came when I attempted to update my address using their form, which contained several errors, including the omission of the letter ‚Äòa‚Äô in ‚Äòaddress.‚Äô It appears this form has been in use since 2015. Consequently, I have decided to register with a different GP.05/08/24Update on changing GPs. Best decision. I won‚Äôt name it because I don't want people joining them. I‚Äôve never set foot inside because I don‚Äôt need to. I can do everything on the app or over the phone. I wish I‚Äôd changed earlier.

Complete jokers.Call up for an appointment on Monday,  told that I'll get a call on Wednesday to confirm a "Hub" appointment for that day. They call on Wednesday to say "woops all the hub appointments are booked, how about Saturday?"Also was offered my 40 year old checkup 2 years late and was given one day option 1 month away. Avoid if you ever want to see a doctor.

Receptionist assistant Mr zaeed seems to be giving misinformation every time theres a general inquiry with his incompetent advices and constant misinformation on any given matter. I'm surprised that despite he's lack of care and attention to his job he's still employed by the surgery. He's not competent for a receptionist duty, lacks basic knowledge and customer services is poor.Just to note the remaining receptionist staff members I found them to be really helpful and professional. Shame I can't say that for Mr Zaeed.Dates times and misinformation details are being logged and will be forwarded to the Clinical commission as to how he's incompetence could lead to patients being at risk or generally just being lied to and misguided by non other than Mr zaeed.

Outstanding Nurse Keisha with treating my daughter with the most amazing care and patience with overcoming her anxiety and fear with having her last immunisation teenage vaccination today, by seeing her two times in one day after being to scared on the first visit today but my daughter went back to Gp again on the same day with the same nurse and she was able to help my daughter to be brave and was outstanding with her calm ways and approach with being a wonderful nurse. Thanks so much

I wish I was exaggerating when I say a large period of my life has been wasted on being on hold with this damn GP. Some of the staff are so useless and clueless, some of them are absolute sweethearts. Most calls I‚Äôve made for checking blood test results I‚Äôve been on hold for over 2 1/2 hours, I walked into the GP in that time and they were all just sitting there and giggling, so lazy!! I‚Äôve been given inaccurate blood test results several times because some of these people are fools. I know the NHS is struggling but it‚Äôs no wonder it‚Äôs happening at his rate with some of the staff this practise has. If you are thinking about joining this GP, don‚Äôt.
Overall the service and care from both clinical and non clinical staff is excellent despite the challenges the NHS is facing. Greatly appreciated.

I called the surgery at 8.28. Callback position 32 by 11.46 it was 2. They then decided to cancel my Callback.  Rang again , position 34 got to position 8 and they cancelled again.  WHY?   have called again and have been put in Callback position 34. WHAT WILL THEY DO NOW

A few years back when I was living in London, a female doctor at this practice suggested I had a very serious psychiatric disorder, (this doctor was not a psychiatrist or psychologist).She had only met me very briefly and should have referred me to someone who specialises in this area, rather than throw out random diagnosis ~ in an area she is unqualified in.At the time I was quite young and didn't speak up for myself or report her. I now see how shocking and inappropriate it was. It caused me a lot of pain and confusion.  Absolutely appalling.
Appalling and dishonest. It's been 4 years and I am still waiting for access to my medical records, presumably so they can edit them so they don't look so terrible.

Waited 20 minutes on the phone today only to be told that l can only hope to get an appointment if l phone up at 8am in the morning on the day.As l carer, l need to take a day off work to take my mum to the gp, the staff member just put the phone down when l tried to explain this.
The booking system is terrible. Why did you get rid of the e consult system, now you can only use it at 8am and sometimes the system doesn‚Äôt even work.

Always had a great experience with the doctors (and for that matter with the people at the end of the phone when I can get to them) but this afternoon I spent well over an hour on hold to try to rearrange an appointment I can't make on Monday only to be cut off with an automated message saying they're sorry they can't answer my call right now...and there's no way I can do anything about it! It's for my kid, who isn't on my NHS app, so I can't fix it that way, and I'm not going to be near the practice before my appointment so won't be able to tell them I can't make it, so not only have they wasted my time but I'm going to end up accidentally wasting their time as well, it feels like a lose lose for everyone!

I was registered with this practice for 3 months and never managed to get through to book an appointment, there is no link to the online form for online assessments.I have subsequently just registered with a new doctors, got accepted and booked an appointment for next week in the last two hours.

I must express my profound disappointment with the service I received. It's disheartening to say that my experience with the doctors at this establishment was nothing short of appalling. From the moment I stepped in, it was evident that they lacked any semblance of interest in their patients' well-being.The lack of empathy and concern displayed by the doctors was truly disconcerting. It felt as though they were merely going through the motions, with no genuine intention to provide assistance or support. Despite attempting to articulate my concerns, I was met with indifference and a dismissive attitude.What struck me the most was their apparent disregard for the Hippocratic Oath and the fundamental principles of medical care. As a patient seeking help and guidance, I expected to be treated with respect and dignity. However, what I encountered was a stark contrast to this expectation.Furthermore, the overall atmosphere of the facility was unwelcoming and sterile, devoid of the warmth and compassion one would hope to find in a healthcare setting. It's disheartening to witness such a blatant disregard for the holistic well-being of patients.In conclusion, I cannot in good conscience recommend this establishment to anyone seeking medical assistance. The lack of genuine care and professionalism exhibited by the doctors is deeply troubling and does a disservice to those in need of medical attention. It is my sincere hope that the necessary steps are taken to address these deficiencies and ensure that all patients are treated with the compassion and respect they deserve.
It is impossible to reach the practice on the phone. I have tried to call them during their opening times the last 2 weeks with no luck.

I've been with this practice since 1997 and it's got gradually worse. I don't blame the Drs and nurses as they have always been beyond excellent and genuinely caring. I blame the Tory Government and senior NHS 'management' for underfunding and implementing expensive systems which are beyond useless. I'm always encouraged to book online or by the app and every time I do all they can offer is a smear test appointment. I'm a middle aged man and even though not medically trained,  confident that I don't need one of those.Suffering the lottery of calling on a specific hour in the morning to book an appointment and not getting through is frustrating and unacceptable.
My local doctors
Amazing service always.  Karen the patient is absolutely patient, friendly and always provides with so much help when you call.

All of their opening times online are different so you never know when they‚Äôre opening, absolutely no way to book an advanced appointment at all, only same-day and even if you call exactly when they open you can expect to be on hold for an hour or more only to be told there‚Äôs nothing available. Absolutely appalling, I‚Äôve never experienced such wilful uselessness, especially when it comes to something as important as healthcare. Try somewhere else.
It‚Äôs impossible to book an appointment. E-Consults appear to be permanently unavailable. The phone line answers with a 2-min long automated message and then keeps you on hold indefinitely.

Website not available for e-consult and already got cut off this morning from the telephone waiting to speak to a member of staff about my 75 year old mother who can barely walk, lost her appetite and struggling to take her medication, please advise.

I think they only have 1 doctor in their practice. Doesn‚Äôt matter what time you called. Always no appointments available. Try to call back tomorrow. Even if you are the 1st person to call in the morning. üò¢üò¢üò¢.
Honestly, the most ridiculous service. Cannot get through to them at all. Waiting each time for an hour! The e-consultation form is from 8 to 8.15am. How atrocious is that!
I needed to see the doctor urgently the receptionist was very helpfulDr at the time attended my daughter with care straight awayBest service

Everytime i phone them to make an appointment they are always fully booked. They take soo long to answer the call and  every single time fully booked. No appointments anymore.  You have to do it online.

This is a great doctors surgery. All the doctors are lovely and the nurses and receptionists.if I need help I do a e consult form and they always get back to me. I recently had covid and the doctors  was great in getting  my astma medication  to me and supported  me when I phoned in a panic more then once during having covid.there isn't enough  doctors  snd nurses in the NHS and we all have to realise they are trying  their best to keep an all well. I love this gp surgery. Thank u mission practice all your support
Especially Mr Jeff Lovemore works perfectly and quickly, thanks...

Can't get a booking and the admin staff are really not helpful.Edited to one star: Wouldn't see my 3 month old son. Asked us to do an e-consultation (the link wouldn't work). I have been going to this GP practice for many years and the GPs and nurses are always very caring, friendly and kind. I feel that they really care about what is wrong with you and want to make sure you get the help or referral you need. Plus they are clearly excellent and experienced doctors. It has been more tricky to get face to face appointments since Covid but they do call you back fairly quickly when you send the online request, so you only go in when you actually need to; sometimes they can assess certain things over the phone and save everyone's time. Would not go anywhere else!

I have never managed to get an appointment here. They never pick up the phone, ever. If you call at 8am it‚Äôs already booked up and you‚Äôll never speak to a human. Have only managed to get appointments through 111. Don‚Äôt even bother.

My son has been having temperature for 4days i called the GP surgery at 8am on monday morning as this so called e consult is never available so this admin staff who took my call asked me what i was calling for I explained my son has been having high temperature and continuous cough she ask what the temp was i told her 38.1 she replied 38.1 is not a high temperature is she having a laugh she clearly has no background of medical so who is she to advise me 38.1 is NOT a temperature!! It was a middle aged lady short hair with glasses sitting at the reception please avoid going to her ,So I decided to take my son to a&e get him treated he was given pen v antibiotics thank god he has recovered now. This surgery has gone down hill since dr mead and dr kenedy left so avoid going there i will be contacting CQC about this surgery
i have tried for 3 days to speak to someone and as a carer. it's a shamble.
Basically impossible even to be answered at the phone
Terrible! Worst service ever received. This place needs to change ASAP. Was really good back in the days
Almost impossible to get through on the phone. Reception staff discourage appointments if you can get through after waiting an hour on hold or the phone doesn't automatically hang up while on hold

When I moved to Bethnal Green 2020 I chose mission practice based on the name and location...thank goodness I didn't read any of these emotionally charged reviews!Yes, the 8am phone call/e consult race is stress inducing.However they are good team of humans, trying their best to help.I have lucked out with Dr Spronk, who is an outstanding medical professional...why? Because he is genuine, caring and HUMAN. I felt HEARD.  He gave me the time I needed to share. Which, when you are in pain and stress, is half the healing journey.I get it, people are ill and in pain..but Slander doesn't bring change. Support does.Mission Practice  thank you for doing your best, and for helping me.love and blessings to all in the community.
Its becoming one of the worst GP in towerhamlets, the appointment service is terrible, can't get through to anyone on the phone and the online e consult is always temporary out of service

Very bad GP from reception to doctors, they don‚Äôt have any experience to be doctor. Call up all day always busy , when we can see doctor but they just said nothing wrong with my son ankle injury and they will refer my son to physical but no one call and then I try to call private physical , physical check and give me report :  A.C.E. Physiotherapy Bethnal Green  Energie Fitness  Pill Box  115 Coventry I write to confirm that I saw My son for physiotherapy assessment and treatment with complaint of right lower leg pain following a football injury. Upon assessment it appears that my son is suffering from stress fracture to his distal right supracondylar medial tibial with some calcific deposits. I have therefore advised My son not to take part in any physical activity classes at school for the next 4 weeks following which he will need to be reviewed before he can resume physical activities again. But doctors from this GP told me my son can back to exercise .
Receptionists are extremely dim and lack any interaction skills. Avoid using this doctors at all costs
Routinely waiting for an HOUR to get through just to book an appointment. Appalling "healthcare" system.

Been waiting 3 days for return call due to problem with blood. Decided to phone waiting 30 minutes before being cut off. Decide to walk up to reception from home and  3 staff basically busy doing nothing. I give up. Such a poor advert for NHS.

This practice does not deserve even one star or half a star . If u call them they wont reply even if u stay on the call for 3 hours , useless gp , the doctors are good.You will never be able to find an appointment in this gp

After waiting for 50 minutes on the phone, a rather arrogant gentleman stated that I could either contact 111 or opt for private healthcare. Very frustrating!Just dial 111 this practice is useless.
I'm fairly happy. It's a shame most gps are on the phone now.

Used to be a really good gp practice till covid. The staff they seem to have hired have no respect or care for people at all. The most useless gp practice now. My family are registered to nearby ones that you call anytime and they still give you an appointment or call back. This idiotic place doesn't give anything unless you call them at 8am. The female receptionists are more helpful compared to the male ones at the practice. Who ever is in charge of this practice needs to review their staff and how they work or just shut the practice down. Waste of tax payers money and we can't receive the service and treatments that we require then there's no need for the place to exist.
Hopeless. Holding on got 45mins so far. On line form suspended every day..

The reception team are awful and just don‚Äôt care. After I was on hold for 16 minutes they answered then hung up. This isn‚Äôt the first time don‚Äôt bother when you get through they are hostile and rude. Change your job if you aren‚Äôt happy. Let's start with good points:1) When you eventually do get to see a doctor, they are GENERALLY good, listen to your needs and respond appropriately.That's it for good points. Bad points:1) I have NEVER been to an appointment that hasn't been at least 45 mins (or more) late to be seen.2) Contacting them is a nightmare; habitually in a queue on the phone that lasts for more than 10 minutes (4 times in the last month)3) Getting an appointment is like finding hen's teeth- not enough doctors, and too many patients.4) Some very serious errors made by both doctors and receptionists.For example; I went to the doctor last October after falling and hitting my knee hard; my patella was not in the correct position, but I was told by the doctor "you have knobbly knees" (for the record, the doctor didn't even TOUCH my knee let along examine it). Cue to 3 months later, and I'm still in pain and the bone is still wrong, I go back and am referred for an MRI; the MRI shows that my patella is actually bipartite, and the doctors doesn't know what to do so I have to be referred to a specialist.5) The referral was not processed properly, as I was given misinformation from the reception (asserting that I had been referred when I knew I hadn't been according to the discussion on the phone with the doctor); so there's been a delay of 4 weeks between the MRI and even BEING referred. For an issue I first went to them about in October 2019.4 months of pain and counting. That could have been avoided if the doctors and receptionists actually did their job properly. To say I'm angry is an understatement.

sometimes we notice what goes wrong and overlook what goes well, it is easy to complain and overlook the amazing resources and service available. I can be guilty of this, which is why I am taking the time to write this review. This is an excellent practice, I have been a patient with them for over 15 years, I can not rate them highly enough. I would particularly recommend Dr Rowell, but the other doctors I've seen, Dr Kennedy, Mains, and Little John, are also very good.A close friend of mine recommended this practice, she was their patient from the 1980's when they were based opposite the museum of Childhood. She died a year ago, and without the care of this practice I don't know how I would have coped. From a member of the reception staff offering me tissues and a glass of water, Dr Kennedy offering me words of comfort while I was waiting for another appointment, to Dr Rowell seeing me regularly sometimes weekly,  as well as referring me to bereavement counselling, and Wilma the amazing social prescriber, seeing me and suggesting places I could to for support.They are also linked with the pharmacy downstairs, which is useful and provides linked up care. In addition to the services of the social [rescriber, the offer many clinics and services including blood tests.I consider The Mission Practice to be an essential part of community services in the area, they do an amazing job.
